---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Home" description="Resolute Ambitions removes financial barriers for future U.S. military officers — scholarships for ROTC candidates, service academy hopefuls, and enlisted service members pursuing commissioning.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow">A Scholarship Mission</div>
      <h1>Service should not start with debt.</h1>
      <p>
        Resolute Ambitions provides scholarships to future U.S. military officers — high school candidates pursuing ROTC and service academy preparation, and enlisted service members pursuing commissioning. We exist so the next generation of military leaders can enter the fleet focused on warfighting, not on how to make ends meet.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/donate" class="btn btn-gold">Support a Scholar</a>
        <a href="/programs" class="btn btn-ghost" style="color: #fafaf7 !important; border-color: rgba(250,250,247,0.4);">See Our Programs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow dark">The Problem</div>
      <h2>Most officers begin their service in debt.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Service academies and full ROTC scholarships are limited and highly competitive. The majority of new officers commission through paths that do not cover the cost of their education.
      </p>
      <div class="stats">
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="num">70–75%</span>
          <div class="label">of military officers enter service with student loan debt</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="num">~15%</span>
          <div class="label">of new officers commission through a service academy</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="num">25–27%</span>
          <div class="label">of ROTC scholarship applicants receive an award</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="num">$25k–$40k</span>
          <div class="label">average debt for officers from non-scholarship paths</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
        Military leadership disproportionately comes from middle- and lower-income backgrounds. The cost of college, modest early-career pay, and the practical impossibility of a meaningful side income during active service create a real decision barrier — one that pushes qualified candidates away from a calling they would otherwise answer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="muted">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow dark">Our Response</div>
      <h2>Change the calculus. Then get out of the way.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        We award merit-based scholarships to two groups, with funds paid directly to accredited institutions for tuition, fees, books, room and board, and required testing.
      </p>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="num">Track 01</span>
          <h3>High school candidates</h3>
          <p>
            For juniors and seniors enrolled in or accepted to accredited colleges and universities with ROTC programs, who demonstrate genuine intent to pursue an officer commission.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="num">Track 02</span>
          <h3>Enlisted service members</h3>
          <p>
            For active-duty enlisted in any branch pursuing undergraduate education for commissioning through Green to Gold, STA-21, OCS, OTS, or similar programs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
        <a href="/programs">See selection criteria and eligibility →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container" style="text-align: center;">
      <div class="eyebrow dark">Support the Mission</div>
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">Every dollar funds a future officer.</h2>
      <p class="lede" style="margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">
        Resolute Ambitions runs lean — volunteer board, minimal overhead, scholarship funds paid directly to schools. Your contribution goes to the candidate.
      </p>
      <a href="/donate" class="btn btn-gold">Donate</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
